    "In Sample 1, the treatment reduced participants' belief in their conspiracy theory participants' stated conspiracy by 17.2 units more than the control (95% CI [14.4, 19.9], p <.001, d = 1.22), which translates into a 22.42% decrease in belief among those in treatment (vs. 1.09% in the control).",
